column1: #Text=Robert Jenrick , the new Conservative MP for Newark .
#Text=The Conservative Party has won the Newark , England by-election but with a reduced majority .
#Text=Voters gave 45.03 % of the vote to Robert Jenrick , while the UK Independence Party candidate Roger Helmer came second with 25.91 % of the vote .
#Text=The turnout was 38,707 , 52.67 % of the electorate of 73,486 .

#Text=The by-election was called following the resignation of Patrick Mercer after it was revealed he was paid to lobby and ask questions in Parliament on behalf of the country of Fiji in an investigation by the BBC Panorama programme .
#Text=Jenrick is a 32-year-old who works as managing director of Christie 's auction house .

#Text=After the election result was announced , he said : " I want to thank the prime minister for his personal support to my campaign and I want to thank the government for its commitment to re-building Britain .

column1: #Text=UKIP leader Nigel Farage said the party had run a " stunning campaign " :
#Text=" We 've been up against probably the biggest ever Conservative machine , defending about their 40th safest seat in the country .

column3:

#Text=The Liberal Democrat candidate , David Watts , said coming in sixth place  was n't a good result , but smaller parties often get squeezed in by-elections and that 's what 's happened to us here " .

column1: #Text=He said the independent campaign by Paul Baggaley had got a lot of support , and " a lot of our voters had transferred to vote against UKIP to make sure UKIP did n't get elected " .

#Text=Grant Shapps from the Conservative Party said the surge of support for UKIP after the European elections was now " going backwards " , while Nigel Farage said Conservative MPs in more marginal seats would be filled with " sheer horror " at UKIP 's success .
